
@startuml
' LabTracker Class Diagram

class Doctor {
  - practitionerNumber: String
  - fullName: String
  - address: String
  - phoneNumber: String
  - signature: Image
}

class Patient {
  - healthNumber: String
  - firstName: String
  - lastName: String
  - dateOfBirth: Date
  - address: String
  - phoneNumber: String
}

class Requisition {
  - validityDate: Date
  - repetitionCount: Integer
  - repetitionInterval: IntervalType
  - tests: List<Test>
  - doctor: Doctor
  - patient: Patient
}

enum IntervalType {
  WEEKLY, MONTHLY, HALF_YEARLY, YEARLY
}

class Test {
  - testName: String
  - duration: Integer
  - testGroup: TestGroup
  - isWalkIn: Boolean
  - requiresAppointment: Boolean
  - requiresSampleDropOff: Boolean
}

class TestGroup {
  - groupName: String
  - tests: List<Test>
}

class Appointment {
  - confirmationNumber: String
  - appointmentDate: Date
  - startTime: Time
  - endTime: Time
  - labName: String
  - labRegistrationNumber: String
  - requisition: Requisition
  - fee: Double
}

class Lab {
  - address: String
  - businessHoursStart: Time
  - businessHoursEnd: Time
  - registrationNumber: String
  - feeStructure: Map<String, Double>
}

class TestResult {
  - resultStatus: ResultStatus
  - report: String
  - test: Test
  - patient: Patient
}

enum ResultStatus {
  POSITIVE, NEGATIVE, INCONCLUSIVE, PENDING
}

' Relationships

Doctor "1" --> "1" Requisition : creates
Patient "1" --> "1" Requisition : submits
Requisition "1" --> "*" Test : contains
Test "1" --> "1" TestGroup : belongs to
Requisition "1" --> "1" Appointment : schedules (optional)
Appointment "1" --> "1" Lab : at
Test "1" --> "1" TestResult : has
TestResult "1" --> "1" Patient : for
TestResult "1" --> "1" Doctor : viewable by
TestResult "1" --> "1" Patient : viewable by
@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Doctor**: Holds all personal info and digital signature.
- **Patient**: Contains personal and health-related details.
- **Requisition**: Central entity linking doctor, patient, and tests. It includes repetition logic and constraints.
- **Test**: Each test belongs to a group, has a duration, and has specific scheduling rules.
- **TestGroup**: Groups tests that can be combined in one requisition.
- **Appointment**: Created from a requisition; has time, lab info, and fees.
- **Lab**: Has business hours and fee structure.
- **TestResult**: Stores results and reports for each test.
- **ResultStatus**: Enum to define the possible result types.

